  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\n**Q: Why should this feature exist?**\r\nA: In the next step of [Ethereum](etherscan.io/address/0x46403e94529fc04d04c9c393beab1d050ef06409#code), smart contracts should run in eWASM bytecode rather than EVM bytecode, for scalability and security.  I have implemented an EVM-to-eWASM bytecode translator that can generate eWASM smart contracts from EVM bytecode directly with correctness. Developers can use the most of EVM infrastructures to develop and interact the eWASM contracts, e.g., Web3. \r\nCheck [https://github.com/Kenun99/ethsema](https://github.com/Kenun99/ethsema) for more details. \r\nCurrently, the eWASM fork of go-ethereum is out-of-date. It is important for Ethereum2.0 to develop a new eWASM client.  \r\n\r\n\r\n**Q: What are the use-cases?**\r\nRun eWASM smart contracts.\r\nWe can integrate EthSema (https://github.com/Kenun99/ethsema) to convert EVM smart contract to eWASM just-in-time and execute eWASM bytecode.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\n**Q:Do you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?**\r\nA:We need to make go-ethereum to provide a new virtual machine to execute smart contracts. \r\n\r\n**Q:Are you willing to implement this feature?**\r\nA:Probably.",
