    "body": "> It is important for Ethereum2.0 to develop a new eWASM client.\r\n\r\nEwasm is not part of the official roadmap for Eth2. The last discussions on that topic revolved around the idea of using ewasm for the other shards. But since then the roadmap has changed and those other shards which are going to be introduced in phase1 are kept data-only, no execution. Closing the issue for now. It can be re-opened if at some point execution shards were back on the table for eth2.",
